geography_levels.name: United States
geography_levels.description: The entire United States, including the 50 states, District of Columbia, and territories. The highest level in the Census Bureau's geographic hierarchy.

geography_levels.name: Region
geography_levels.description: Four groupings of states established by the Census Bureau for the presentation of census data: Northeast, Midwest, South, and West regions.

geography_levels.name: Division
geography_levels.description: Nine groupings of states and the District of Columbia that are subdivisions of the four census regions, such as New England and Middle Atlantic divisions.

geography_levels.name: State
geography_levels.description: The primary legal divisions of the United States, including the 50 states, District of Columbia, and territories treated as state equivalents.

geography_levels.name: County
geography_levels.description: The primary legal divisions of most states, including counties, parishes in Louisiana, boroughs in Alaska, and other equivalent entities.

geography_levels.name: County Subdivision
geography_levels.description: Primary divisions of counties including minor civil divisions (MCDs) such as towns and townships, and census county divisions (CCDs) in states without adequate MCDs.

geography_levels.name: County Subdivision (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of county subdivisions that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Subminor Civil Division
geography_levels.description: Legal subdivisions of minor civil divisions, such as subbarrios in Puerto Rico, providing a more detailed level of local government organization.

geography_levels.name: Voting District
geography_levels.description: Geographic entities such as precincts, wards, and election districts established by state governments for conducting elections.

geography_levels.name: Voting District (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of voting districts that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Block
geography_levels.description: The smallest geographic unit used by the Census Bureau for tabulation of 100-percent data. Blocks are bounded by visible features like streets and nonvisible boundaries like property lines.

geography_levels.name: Census Tract
geography_levels.description: Small, relatively permanent statistical subdivisions of counties with populations typically between 1,200 and 8,000 people, designed to be relatively stable over time.

geography_levels.name: Block Group
geography_levels.description: Statistical divisions of census tracts, generally defined to contain between 600 and 3,000 people, used to present sample data and control block numbering.

geography_levels.name: Tabulation Block
geography_levels.description: Specific census blocks used for tabulation purposes, representing the smallest geographic units for which the Census Bureau collects and tabulates data.

geography_levels.name: Tabulation Block (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of tabulation blocks that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Place
geography_levels.description: Incorporated places and census designated places (CDPs) that represent concentrations of population, including cities, towns, villages, and other legally incorporated areas.

geography_levels.name: Place (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of places that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Consolidated City
geography_levels.description: A unit of local government where the functions of an incorporated place and its county have merged, resulting in a single consolidated government.

geography_levels.name: Consolidated City (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of consolidated cities that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Alaska Native Regional Corporation
geography_levels.description: Twelve regional corporations created pursuant to the Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act to conduct for-profit and nonprofit affairs of Alaska Natives within defined regions.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area/alaska native area/hawaiian home land
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area/Hawaiian Home Land
geography_levels.description: Areas that have been set aside by the United States for the use of tribes, including federally recognized American Indian reservations, Alaska Native areas, and Hawaiian home lands.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area/alaska native area (reservation only)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area (Reservation Only)
geography_levels.description: Federal reservations that are territory over which American Indian tribes have governmental authority, excluding off-reservation trust lands.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area (off-reservation trust land only)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area (Off-Reservation Trust Land Only)
geography_levels.description: Areas for which the United States holds title in trust for the benefit of a tribe or individual American Indian, located outside reservation boundaries.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area/alaska native area (statistical entity only)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area (Statistical Entity Only)
geography_levels.description: Statistical entities for American Indian tribes including tribal designated statistical areas, Oklahoma tribal statistical areas, and Alaska Native village statistical areas.

geography_levels.name: Tribal Census Tract
geography_levels.description: Statistical subdivisions of American Indian reservations and off-reservation trust lands, defined independently of standard county-based census tracts.

geography_levels.name: Tribal Block Group
geography_levels.description: Statistical divisions of tribal census tracts, defined independently of standard county-based block groups to provide data for tribal areas.

geography_levels.name: American Indian Area Tribal Subdivision
geography_levels.description: Legal administrative subdivisions of American Indian reservations and off-reservation trust lands that serve social, cultural, or economic purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area tribal subdivision (or part)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area Tribal Subdivision (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of tribal subdivisions that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area/alaska native area/hawaiian home land (or part)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area/Hawaiian Home Land County
geography_levels.description: State portions of American Indian areas, Alaska Native areas, and Hawaiian home lands for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: state american indian area/alaska native area/hawaiian home land (or part)
geography_levels.name: State American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area/Hawaiian Home Land (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: General state portions of American Indian areas, Alaska Native areas, and Hawaiian home lands, serving as a broader category for tribal areas within states.

geography_levels.query_name: state american indian area/alaska native area (reservation or statistical entity only) (or part)
geography_levels.name: State American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area (Reservation Or Statistical Entity Only) (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of American Indian reservations and statistical entities, excluding off-reservation trust lands, for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: state american indian area (off-reservation trust land only)/hawaiian home land (or part)
geography_levels.name: State American Indian Area (Off-Reservation Trust Land Only)/Hawaiian Home Land (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of American Indian off-reservation trust lands and Hawaiian home lands, distinct from reservation areas, for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area/alaska native area (reservation only) (or part)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area (Reservation Only) (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of American Indian reservations and Alaska Native areas, excluding trust lands and statistical entities, for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area (off-reservation trust land only) (or part)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area (Off-Reservation Trust Land Only) (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of American Indian off-reservation trust lands only, excluding reservation areas, for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: american indian area/alaska native area (statistical entity only) (or part)
geography_levels.name: American Indian Area/Alaska Native Area (Statistical Entity Only) (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of American Indian and Alaska Native statistical entities, excluding reservations and trust lands, for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Hawaiian Home Land (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Areas held in trust for Native Hawaiians by the State of Hawaii, pursuant to the Hawaiian Homes Commission Act of 1920, as amended.

geography_levels.name: Alaska Native Village Corporation (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of Alaska Native village corporations, which are local entities created under the Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act.

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Statistical Area/Micropolitan Statistical Area
geography_levels.description: Core Based Statistical Areas consisting of counties associated with at least one urban area of 10,000+ population, plus adjacent counties with high economic integration.

geography_levels.name: State-Metropolitan Statistical Area/Micropolitan Statistical Area
geography_levels.description: Core Based Statistical Areas within state boundaries

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Statistical Area
geography_levels.description: Core Based Statistical Areas associated with at least one urban area of 50,000+ population, comprising central counties plus adjacent economically integrated counties.

geography_levels.name: Micropolitan Statistical Area
geography_levels.description: Core Based Statistical Areas associated with at least one urban area of 10,000-49,999 population, comprising central counties plus adjacent economically integrated counties.

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Statistical Area Principal City
geography_levels.description: The largest incorporated place with 10,000+ population in a metropolitan statistical area, or other qualifying places based on population and employment criteria.

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Division
geography_levels.description: Smaller groupings of counties within a metropolitan statistical area containing a single core with 2.5+ million population, representing employment centers.

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Division Principal City
geography_levels.description: The main city or town that represents an employment center within a metropolitan division, plus adjacent cities and towns with commuting ties.

geography_levels.name: Micropolitan Statistical Area Principal City
geography_levels.description: The largest incorporated place with 10,000+ population in a micropolitan statistical area, or other qualifying places based on population and employment criteria.

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Statistical Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of metropolitan statistical areas, representing the part of an MSA that falls within a specific state for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Micropolitan Statistical Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of micropolitan statistical areas, representing the part of a micropolitan area that falls within a specific state for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: metropolitan statistical area/micropolitan statistical area principal city (or part)
geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Statistical Area/Micropolitan Statistical Area Principal City (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of principal cities within Core Based Statistical Areas, representing the main urban centers within CBSAs for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Metropolitan Division (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of metropolitan divisions, representing parts of metropolitan divisions that fall within specific states for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Combined Statistical Area
geography_levels.description: Two or more adjacent Core Based Statistical Areas that have substantial employment interchange, retaining separate identities within the larger combined area.

geography_levels.name: Combined Statistical Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of combined statistical areas, representing parts of CSAs that fall within specific states for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: new england city and town area
geography_levels.name: New England City And Town Area
geography_levels.description: Alternative geographic entities in New England based on cities and towns rather than counties, similar in concept to Core Based Statistical Areas.

geography_levels.query_name: new england city and town area (or part)
geography_levels.name: New England City And Town Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of New England City and Town Areas, representing parts of NECTAs that fall within specific states for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.query_name: combined new england city and town area
geography_levels.name: Combined New England City And Town Area
geography_levels.description: Two or more adjacent New England City and Town Areas that have substantial employment interchange, similar to Combined Statistical Areas.

geography_levels.query_name: combined new england city and town area (or part)
geography_levels.name: Combined New England City And Town Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of combined New England City and Town Areas, representing parts of combined NECTAs that fall within specific states.

geography_levels.name: Urban Area
geography_levels.description: Densely developed territory with at least 2,500 people, encompassing residential, commercial, and other nonresidential urban land uses representing the urban footprint.

geography_levels.name: Urban Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: State portions of urban areas, representing parts of urban areas that fall within specific states for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Urban Cluster
geography_levels.description: Densely developed territory with at least 2,500 but less than 50,000 people, representing smaller urban concentrations than urbanized areas.

geography_levels.name: Congressional District
geography_levels.description: The 435 areas from which people are elected to the U.S. House of Representatives, with each district designed to have equal population within each state.

geography_levels.name: Congressional District (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of congressional districts that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Congressional District (111th Congress)
geography_levels.description: Congressional district boundaries as they existed during the 111th Congress (2009-2011), used for historical comparison purposes.

geography_levels.name: State Legislative District (Upper Chamber)
geography_levels.description: Areas from which members are elected to state senate or equivalent upper chambers of state legislatures, including unicameral legislatures.

geography_levels.name: State Legislative District (Upper Chamber) (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of state legislative districts (upper chamber) that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: State Legislative District (Lower Chamber)
geography_levels.description: Areas from which members are elected to state house of representatives, assembly, or equivalent lower chambers of state legislatures.

geography_levels.name: State Legislative District (Lower Chamber) (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of state legislative districts (lower chamber) that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: Public Use Microdata Area
geography_levels.description: Statistical geographic areas with at least 100,000 people, used for disseminating Public Use Microdata Sample files while protecting confidentiality.

geography_levels.name: Zip Code Tabulation Area
geography_levels.description: Approximate area representations of U.S. Postal Service five-digit ZIP Code service areas, created using whole blocks for statistical data presentation.

geography_levels.name: Zip Code Tabulation Area (Or Part)
geography_levels.description: Portions of ZIP Code Tabulation Areas that may be split by other geographic boundaries for statistical presentation purposes.

geography_levels.name: School District (Elementary)
geography_levels.description: Geographic entities that provide public educational services to the lower grade/age levels, typically kindergarten through grades 6-8.

geography_levels.name: School District (Secondary)
geography_levels.description: Geographic entities that provide public educational services to the upper grade/age levels, typically grades 7-12 or 9-12.

geography_levels.name: School District (Unified)
geography_levels.description: Geographic entities that provide public educational services to children of all school ages, typically prekindergarten or kindergarten through grade 12.

geography_levels.name: School District (Administrative Unit)
geography_levels.description: Administrative units that oversee school district operations and may provide services to multiple school districts within a region.
